President Obama has issued a statement expressing his pride in the passage of The Global Food Security Act of 2016 by Congress. The act puts into law Feed the Future, a global hunger and food security initiative. The President thanked the co-sponsors of the legislation and acknowledged the leaders of the Foreign Affairs and Agriculture Committees for their leadership. He highlighted the positive impact of this initiative in increasing economic growth and combating global hunger, poverty, and malnutrition. The President believes that with continued effort and support, global poverty and hunger can be ended within our lifetimes.